<figureCitation id="57952A2BFFE3FFF9FDE556CCFD5A2FA0" box="[561,674,1152,1179]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="27.[189,231,1963,1989]" captionTargetBox="[195,1393,382,1790]" captionTargetId="figure-15@27.[189,1399,376,1834]" captionTargetPageId="27" captionText="Fig. 15. Neostasina toronegro sp. nov., holotype, ♀ (MCZ 30719). A. Habitus, dorsal view. B. Habitus, ventral view. C. Epigyne, ventral view. D. Vulva, dorsal view. Scale bars: A−B = 2 mm; C−D = 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6608338" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6608338/files/figure.png" pageId="28" pageNumber="194">Figs 15D</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="57952A2BFFE3FFF9FD7A56CCFD332FA0" box="[686,715,1152,1179]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="28.[189,233,849,875]" captionTargetBox="[204,1376,310,784]" captionTargetId="figure-134@28.[189,1399,286,785]" captionTargetPageId="28" captionText="Fig. 16. Neostasina toronegro sp. nov., A−B: holotype, ♀ (MCZ 30719). A. Epigyne, ventral view. B. Vulva, dorsal view. C. Schematic course of internal duct system. Abbreviations: ar = anterior rim; CD = copulatory duct; FD = fertilization duct; GP = glandular projection; LL = lateral lobe; MS = median septum. Scale bars = 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6607956" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6607956/files/figure.png" pageId="28" pageNumber="194">16</figureCitation>
B−C).
</paragraph>
